descriptionNullable:
**Context**

A dataset of 29843 cat pictures (64x64), compiled together for training models.

**Description** :
The Cat Dataset is a collection of 29,843 color images of cats, intended for training machine learning models for computer vision tasks such as image classification, object detection, and image segmentation. The dataset consists of various breeds, poses, backgrounds, and lighting conditions, providing a diverse representation of cat images.

**Details**

Number of Images: 29,843

Image Size: 64 x 64 pixels

Image Format: PNG

Image Resolution: RGB (3 channels)

**Data Split**

The dataset is divided into the following subsets:

Training Set: 29,843 images (100% of the dataset)

This dataset can be utilized for a variety of computer vision tasks, including but not limited to:

Image Classification: Training models to classify images as containing a cat or not.
Object Detection: Detecting and localizing cats within images.
Image Segmentation: Pixel-level labeling and segmentation of cats in images.
Transfer Learning: Using pre-trained models on this dataset for related computer vision tasks.

**Acknowledgements**
Owner: [AnnikaV9](https://github.com/AnnikaV9)

The dataset was originally found at: https://av9.dev/cat-dataset/
